Package com.github.basking2.sdsai

Class Interval<K extends java.lang.Comparable<K>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.basking2.sdsai.Interval<K>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - 
    public class Interval<K extends java.lang.Comparable<K>>
extends java.lang.Object
    A half-open interval the starts at point a and continues until point b but excluding point b. Because of this, the interval [1, 2) is above the interval [0, 1) but is not above the point 1. This is because the end value, 1, in the interval [0, 1) is excluded while when comparing the point 1 to the start of the interval [1, 2), point 1 is included.

      • containsOrEqual

        public boolean containsOrEqual​(K point)
        Return true if the point equals the min or falls within the range of [min, max). This differs from contains(Comparable) when the interval's min and max are the same value. For these intervals if the point is equal to the min, it is considered "equal" and true is returned.
        Parameters:
        point - The point to check.
        Returns:
        true if the point equals the min or falls within the range of [min, max).

      • contains

        public boolean contains​(K pt)
        Return true if the point falls within the range of [min, max). If the interval has a min and a max that are equal, the point is considered not contained.
        Parameters:
        pt - The point.
        Returns:
        true if the point falls within the range of [min, max).
